univention-gdm (5.0.3-1) unstable; urgency=low
  
  [ Moritz Muehlenhoff ]
  * Add a new Univention Configuration Registry variable, which makes XDMCP
    configurable. By default is is disabled and the login button in the GDM
    "Actions" menu is omitted (Bug #15441)
  * Fix handling of session pre session and post session scripts by replacing the
    self-written mechanism with run-parts. The old approach simply sourced the
    shell script file, which leads to aborts if any of the scripts fails (Bug
    #15296)
  * Add a new UCR variable gdm/session/default, which can be used to configure
    the default GDM session script (Bug #15103)

